	<ol>
		<li>
			<p>
				In some computer programs, a loop is necessary to add a list of numbers.  Consider the cubes of the first 100 integers, <m>1^3, 2^3, 3^3,\cdots ,100^3</m>.
				<ol>
					<li>
						<p>
							Create a matrix of the numbers 1 to 100 and use the sum command to find the sum of the cubes of the numbers.
						</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<p>
							Use a for loop to find the same sum by adding the cubes of the numbers one at a time (onto a cumulative sum).
						</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<p>
							A formula that you may have seen is that the sum of the cubes of the numbers from 1 to <m>n</m> is given by <m>\displaystyle \frac{n^2 (n+1)^2}{4}</m>.  Confirm your sum in the previous parts using this formula.
						</p>
					</li>
				</ol>
			</p>
