			<p>
				In this exercise, you will be comparing the capabilities of the two structures <c>if</c>-<c>else</c> and <c>switch</c>-<c>case</c> by creating two programs.  In each program, prompt the user to enter the last name of one of the last 10 presidents of the United States.  Your programs should display an informative sentence in response, including the presidency number and when he served, or display an error message if the entered name is invalid.  
